CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier November 16, 1940, pg. 8 reads:" Camille Hood; Courier's correspondent in Cincinnati, came to the home office Friday to visit with the staff and get new ideas on her work in Queen City. She was house guest of the T.B. Hamiltons."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Camille Hood in fur stole standing outside door to Pennsylvania Central airplane
